est The sweetest  and in fairest colors dressed.', 63383, 0), (410469, 'Sweet April showers Do bring May flowers.', 12910, 0), (410470, 'Oh  the lovely fickleness of an April day!', 64753, 0), (410471, 'The ides of March are come.', 13, 0), (410472, 'January grey is here  Like a sexton by her grave  February bears the bier  March with grief doth howl and rave  And April weeps - but  O ye hours! Follow with May''s fairest flowers.', 165, 0), (410473, 'Those only deserve a monument who do not need one.', 8948, 0), (410474, 'Monuments! what are they? the very pyramids have forgotten their builders  or to whom they were dedicated. Deeds  not stones  are the true monuments of the great.', 4502, 0), (410475, 'Soldiers  forty centuries are looking down upon you from these pyramids.', 62198, 0), (410476, 'How like a queen comes forth the lonely Moon From the slow opening curtains of the clouds Walking in beauty to her midnight throne!', 64754, 0), (410477, 'He should  as he list  be able to prove the moon is green cheese.', 64755, 0), (410478, 'That orbed maiden  with white fire laden  Whom mortals call the moon.', 165, 0), (410479, 'A truth that''s told with bad intent - beats all the lies you can invent.', 221, 0), (410480, 'An election is a moral horror  as bad as a battle except for the blood  a mud bath for every soul concerned in it.', 266, 0), (410481, 'An improper mind is a perpetual feast.', 1014, 0), (410482, 'Every man has his moral backside too  which he doesn''t expose unnecessarily but keeps covered as long as possible by the trousers of decorum.', 62678, 0), (410483, 'In statesmanship get formalities right  never mind about the moralities.', 286, 0), (410484, 'It is a public scandal that gives offence and it is no sin to sin in secret.', 1695, 0), (410485, 'Moral indignation is  in most cases  2% moral  48% indignation and 50% envy.', 64756, 0), (410486, 'Morality is the theory that every human act must be either right or wrong and that 99% of them are wrong.', 411, 0), (410487, 'Of moral purpose I see no trace in Nature. That is an article of exclusively human manufacture - and very much to our credit.', 63366, 0), (410488, 'One of the misfortunes of our time is that in getting rid of false shame  we have killed off so much real shame as well.', 38498, 0), (410489, 'Straight is the gate  and narrow is the way  which leadeth unto life  and few there be that find it.', 5587, 0), (410490, 'The flea  though he kill none  he does all the harm he can.', 703, 0), (410491, 'The only people who should really sin are the people who can sin with a grin.', 2247, 0), (410492, 'The so-called new morality has too often the old immorality condoned.', 64757, 0), (410493, 'To act without rapacity  to use knowledge with wisdom  to respect interdependence  to operate without hubris and greed are not simply moral imperatives. They are an accurate scientific description of the means of survival.', 63310, 0), (410494, 'If some great power would agree to make me always think what is true and do what is right  on condition of being some sort of clock and wound up every morning before I got out of bed  I should close instantly with the offer.', 63366, 0), (410495, 'We have two kinds of morality side by side: one which we preach but do not practice  and the other which we practice but seldom preach.', 95, 0), (410496, 'There are ten commandments  right? Well  it''s like an exam. You get eight out of ten  you''re just about top of the class.', 19436, 0), (410497, 'A man does not have to be an angel in order to be a saint.', 1006, 0), (410498, 'No man is so exquisitely honest or upright in living but that ten times in his life he might not lawfully be hanged.', 663, 0), (410499, 'It is often easier to fight for principles than to live up to them.', 28686, 0), (410500, 'Only that which does not teach  which does not cry out  which does not condescend  which does not explain  is irresistible.', 62867, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (410501, 'Quality - in its classic Greek sense - how to live with grace and intelligence  with bravery and mercy.', 17594, 0), (410502, 'What is morality in any given time or place? It is what the majority then and there happen to like  and immorality is what they dislike.', 2606, 0), (410503, 'No morality can be founded on authority  even if the authority were divine.', 2814, 0), (410504, 'In any assembly the simplest way to stop transacting business and split the ranks is to appeal to a principle.', 9596, 0), (410505, 'He who would do good to another must do it in minute particulars: general good is the plea of the scoundrel  hypocrite and flatterer. For art and science cannot exist but in minutely organized particulars.', 221, 0), (410506, 'You''ve got to be brave and you''ve got to be bold. Brave enough to take your chance on your own discrimination - what''s right and what''s wrong  what''s good and what''s bad.', 35, 0), (410507, 'Most people sell their souls and live with a good conscience on the proceeds.', 1014, 0), (410508, 'This world is white no longer  and it will never be white again.', 85, 0), (410509, 'Below the navel there is neither religion nor truth.', 8090, 0), (410510, 'It is customary these days to ignore what should be done in favour of what pleases us.', 62134, 0), (410511, 'What is morality but immemorial custom? Conscience is the chief of conservatives.', 1049, 0), (410512, 'What you get free costs too much.', 713, 0), (410513, 'You cannot receive a shock unless you have an electric affinity for that which shocks you.', 1049, 0), (410514, 'Even moderation ought not to be practised to excess.', 33, 0), (410515, 'When a blind man carries the lame man  both go forward.', 1477, 0), (410516, 'I have found by experience that they who have spent all their lives in cities  improve their talents but impair their virtues  and strengthen their minds but weaken their morals.', 432, 0), (410517, 'Shame and guilt are noble emotions essential in the maintenance of civilized society  and vital for the development of some of the most refined and elegant qualities of human potential - generosity  service  self-sacrifice  unselfishness and duty.', 64758, 0), (410518, 'If your morals make you dreary  depend on it they are wrong.', 449, 0), (410519, 'Do not be too moral. You may cheat yourself out of much life. So aim above morality. Be not simply good  be good for something.', 1049, 0), (410520, 'Moral courage is a more rare commodity than bravery in battle or great intelligence.', 1973, 0), (410521, 'Morality is not respectability.', 266, 0), (410522, 'Moral indignation - jealousy with a halo.', 3173, 0), (410523, 'Nobody does nothing for nobody for naught.', 47739, 0), (410524, 'The man who is anybody and who does anything is surely going to be criticized  vilified  and misunderstood. This is part of the penalty for greatness  and every man understands  too  that it is no proof of greatness.', 4, 0), (410525, 'Morality is a private and costly luxury.', 63668, 0), (410526, '"Tut  tut  child " said the Duchess. "Everything''s got a moral if only you can find it."', 1253, 0), (410527, 'I never did  or countenanced  in public life  a single act inconsistent with the strictest good faith  having never believed there was one code of morality for a public  and another for a private man.', 1207, 0), (410528, 'Dr. Johnson''s morality was as English an article as a beefsteak.', 64440, 0), (410529, 'To give a man full knowledge of true morality  I would send him to no other book than the New Testament.', 2375, 0), (410530, 'We know no spectacle so ridiculous as the British public in one of its periodical fits of morality.', 62487, 0), (410531, 'Morality is the best of all devices for leading mankind by the nose.', 11, 0), (410532, 'Do not be too moral. You may cheat yourself out of much life so. Aim above morality. Be not simply good  be good for something.', 1049, 0), (410533, 'Now the frosty stars are gone: I have watched them one by one  Fading on the shores of Dawn. Round and full the glorious sun Walks with level step the spray  Through his vestibule of Day.', 57546, 0), (410534, 'The grey-ey''d morn smiles on the frowning night  Chequering the eastern clouds with streaks of light.', 13, 0), (410535, 'Lose an hour in the morning  and you will be all day hunting for it.', 25969, 0), (410536, 'There never was night that had no morn.', 15444, 0), (410537, 'Weeping may endure for a night  but joy cometh in the morning.', 5587, 0), (410538, 'Sadness flies on the wings of the morning  and out of the heart of darkness comes the light.', 42142, 0), (410539, 'Out of the scabbard of the night  By God''s hand drawn  Flashes his shining sword of light  And lo  the dawn!', 64759, 0), (410540, 'For what human ill does not dawn seem to be an alleviation?', 744, 0), (410541, 'The weariest night  the longest day  sooner or later must perforce come to an end.', 64760, 0), (410542, 'Beware of desp''rate steps  the darkest day lived till tomorrow will have pass''d away.', 8676, 0), (410543, 'Have hope. Though clouds environs now  And gladness hides her face in scorn  Put thou the shadow from thy brow- No night but hath its morn.', 62240, 0), (410544, 'Snow endures but for a season  and joy comes with the morning.', 267, 0), (410545, 'The morning is wiser than the evening.', 24628, 0), (410546, 'For the mind disturbed  the still beauty of dawn is nature''s finest balm.', 12943, 0), (410547, 'Hold your head high  stick your chest out. You can make it. It gets dark sometimes  but morning comes. ... Keep hope alive.', 23411, 0), (410548, 'Each day the world is born anew for him who takes it rightly.', 1247, 0), (410549, 'It is a common experience that a problem difficult at night is resolved in the morning after the committee of sleep has worked on it.', 1070, 0), (410550, 'Each day is a new life. Seize it. Live it.', 64761, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (410551, 'We sail  at sunrise  daily  "outward bound."', 25904, 0), (410552, 'Always begin anew with the day  just as nature does. It is one of the sensible things that nature does.', 2015, 0), (410553, 'With each sunrise  we start anew.', 33, 0), (410554, 'I have always been delighted at the prospect of a new day  a fresh try  one more start  with perhaps a bit of magic waiting somewhere behind the morning.', 47328, 0), (410555, 'Relying on God has to begin all over again every day as if nothing had yet been done.', 26, 0), (410556, 'Have patience with all things  but chiefly have patience with yourself. Do not lose courage in considering your own imperfections  but instantly set about remedying them-every day begin the task anew.', 63291, 0), (410557, 'Each day is a little life  every waking and rising a little birth  every fresh morning a little youth  every going to rest and sleep a little death.', 1304, 0), (410558, 'I love the challenge of starting at zero every day and seeing how much I can accomplish.', 37848, 0), (410559, 'Whether one is twenty  forty  or sixty  whether one has succeeded  failed or just muddled along  whether yesterday was full of sun or storm  or one of those dull days with no weather at all  life begins each morning! ... Each morning is the open door to a new world-new vistas  new aims  new tryings.', 63561, 0), (410560, 'To be seeing the world made new every morning  as if it were the morning of the first day  and then to make the most of it for the individual soul as if each were the last day  is the daily curriculum of the mind''s desire.', 63319, 0), (410561, 'Do not say  "It is morning " and dismiss it with a name of yesterday. See it for the first time as a newborn child that has no name.', 430, 0), (410562, 'God had infinite time to give us.... He cut it up into a near succession of new mornings  and  with each  therefore  a new idea  new inventions  and new applications.', 760, 0), (410563, 'We are new every day.', 64762, 0), (410564, 'No matter how big or soft or warm your bed is  you still have to get out of it.', 64763, 0), (410565, 'Spill not the morning (the quintessence of the day!) in recreations  for sleep is a recreation. Add not  therefore  sauce to sauce. ... Pastime  like wine  is poison in the morning. It is then good husbandry to sow the head  which hath lain fallow all night  with some serious work.', 1348, 0), (410566, 'Do not shorten the morning by getting up late  look upon it as the quintessence of life  and to a certain extent sacred.', 1304, 0), (410567, 'Let us then be up and doing  with a heart for any fate.', 147, 0), (410568, 'He''d jolt up in bed every morning  sit quietly for a moment  and you could feel those wheels spinning in his mind as he planned his day. Then he''d hit the floor almost on the run.', 64764, 0), (410569, 'Clay lies still  but blood''s a rover Breath''s a ware that will not keep. Up lad: when the journey''s over There''ll be time enough to sleep.', 7209, 0), (410570, 'Even if a farmer intends to loaf  he gets up in time to get an early start.', 20175, 0), (410571, 'Wake at dawn with a winged heart and give thanks for another day of loving.', 81, 0), (410572, 'I thank You God for this most amazing day  for the leaping greenly spirits of trees and a blue true dream of sky  and for everything which is natural which is infinite which is yes.', 37, 0), (410573, 'I get up and I bless the light thin clouds and the first twittering of birds  and the breathing air and smiling face of the hills.', 7895, 0), (410574, 'I''m a most lucky and thankful woman. Lucky and thankful for each morning I wake up. For three wonderful daughters and one son. For an understanding and very loving husband with whom I''ve shared fifty-two blessed years  all in good health.', 64765, 0), (410575, 'If God adds another day to our life  let us receive it gladly.', 62237, 0), (410576, 'Here we stand between two eternities of darkness. What are we to do with this glory while it is still ours?', 9354, 0), (410577, 'Your morning thoughts may determine your conduct for the day. Optimistic thoughts will make your day bright and productive  while pessimistic thinking will make it dull and wasteful. Face each day cheerfully  smilingly and courageously  and it will naturally follow that your work will be a real pleasure and progress will be a delightful accomplishment.', 64766, 0), (410578, 'You should always know when you''re shifting gears in life. You should leave your era  it should never leave you.', 62943, 0), (410579, 'The first thing each morning  and the last thing each night  suggest to yourself specific ideas that you wish to embody in your character and personality. Address such suggestions to yourself  silently or aloud  until they are deeply impressed upon your mind.', 31710, 0), (410580, 'Everyday ask yourself the question  "Do I want to experience Peace of Mind or do I want to experience Conflict ?"', 62307, 0), (410581, 'It was only a sunny smile  And little it cost in the giving. But like morning light  it scattered the night  And made the day worth living.', 33, 0), (410582, 'To get up each morning with the resolve to be happy ... is to set our own conditions to the events of each day. To do this is to condition circumstances instead of being conditioned by them.', 63532, 0), (410583, 'Today is a new day. You will get out of it just what you put into it. ... If you have made mistakes  even serious mistakes  there is always another chance for you. And supposing you have tried and failed again and again  you may have a fresh start any moment you choose  for this thing that we call "failure" is not the falling down  but the staying down.', 3277, 0), (410584, 'When you rise in the morning  form a resolution to make the day a happy one for a fellow creature.', 9771, 0), (410585, 'As soon as you open your eyes in the morning  you can square away for a happy and successful day. It''s the mood and the purpose at the inception of each day that are the important facts in charting your course for the day. We can always square away for a fresh start  no matter what the past has been.', 62529, 0), (410586, 'This is the beginning of a new day. God has given me this day to use as I will. I can waste it or use it for good  but what I do today is important  because I am exchanging a day of my life for it! When tomorrow comes  this day will be gone forever  leaving in its place something that I have traded for it. I want it to be gain  and not loss  good  and not evil  success  and not failure  in order that I shall not regret the price I have paid for it.', 33, 0), (410587, 'I think in terms of the day''s resolutions  not the year''s.', 19834, 0), (410588, 'Every new day begins with possibilities. It''s up to us to fill it with the things that move us toward progress and peace.', 1727, 0), (410589, 'Here hath been dawning another blue day: think  wilt thou let it slip useless away?', 3061, 0), (410590, 'Be pleasant until ten o''clock in the morning and the rest of the day will take care of itself.', 4, 0), (410591, 'Today a thousand doors of enterprise are open to you  inviting you to useful work. To live at this time is an inestimable privilege  and a sacred obligation devolves upon you to make right use of your opportunities. Today is the day in which to attempt and achieve something worthwhile.', 31710, 0), (410592, 'Get out of bed forcing a smile. You may not smile because you are cheerful  but if you will force yourself to smile you''ll... be cheerful because you smile. Repeated experiments prove that when man assumes the facial expression of a given mental mood  any given mood  then that mental mood itself will follow.', 64767, 0), (410593, 'He who every morning plans the transactions of the day and follows that plan carries thread that will guide him through the labyrinth of the most busy life.', 98, 0), (410594, 'A man without a plan for the day is lost before he starts.', 64768, 0), (410595, 'Never be afraid to sit awhile and think.', 64136, 0), (410596, 'Only the thinking man lives his life  the thoughtless man''s life passes him by.', 20540, 0), (410597, 'My credo is etched on my mirror in my bathroom and I see it when I brush my teeth in the morning. It says  "Don''t worry  Be Happy  Feel Good." When you see that first thing  and you reflect on it  the rest of the day seems to glide by pretty well.', 64769, 0), (410598, 'Only that day dawns to which we are awake.', 1049, 0), (410599, 'The day returns and brings us the petty round of irritating concerns and duties. Help us to play the man  help us to perform them with laughter and kind faces  let cheerfulness abound with industry. Give us to go blithely on our business all this day  bring us to our resting beds weary and content and undishonored  and grant us in the end the gift of sleep.', 449, 0), (410600, 'A day dawns  quite like other days  in it  a single hour comes  quite like other hours  but in that day and in that hour the chance of a lifetime faces us.', 63768, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (410601, 'One never knows what each day is going to bring. The important thing is to be open and ready for it.', 19834, 0), (410602, 'Great opportunities come to all  but many do not know they have met them. The only preparation to take advantage of them is ... to watch what each day brings.', 64770, 0), (410603, 'There will be something  anguish or elation  that is peculiar to this day alone. I rise from sleep and say: Hail to the morning! Come down to me  my beautiful unknown.', 64771, 0), (410604, 'The sun is new each day.', 1083, 0), (410605, 'Someday the sun is going to shine down on me in some faraway place.', 18404, 0), (410606, 'With every rising of the sun  think of your life as just begun.', 33, 0), (410607, 'I feel very happy to see the sun come up every day. I feel happy to be around. ... I like to take this day- any day-and go to town with it.', 9013, 0), (410608, 'Look to the East  where up the lucid sky The morning climbs! The day shall yet be fair.', 64772, 0), (410609, 'Each golden sunrise ushers in new opportunities for those who retain faith in themselves  and keep their chins up.... Meet the sunrise with confidence. Fill every golden minute with right thinking and worthwhile endeavor. Do this and there will be joy for you in each golden sunset.', 63083, 0), (410610, 'Today a new sun rises for me  everything lives  everything is animated  everything seems to speak to me of my passion  everything invites me to cherish it.', 64773, 0), (410611, 'What humbugs we are  who pretend to live for Beauty  and never see the Dawn!', 1014, 0), (410612, 'Sunrise: day''s great progenitor.', 91, 0), (410613, 'Put yourself in competition with yourself each day. Each morning look back upon your work of yesterday and then try to beat it.', 19187, 0), (410614, 'The morning has gold in its mouth.', 5058, 0), (410615, 'Do you know what the greatest test is? Do you still get excited about what you do when you get up in the morning?', 9554, 0), (410616, 'Oft when the white  still dawn lifted the skies and pushed the hills apart  I have felt it like a glory in my heart.', 545, 0), (410617, 'Sometimes I have believed as many as six impossible things before breakfast.', 1253, 0), (410618, 'The mind is found most acute and most uneasy in the morning. Uneasiness is  indeed  a species of sagacity-a passive sagacity. Fools are never uneasy.', 62224, 0), (410619, 'Day''s sweetest moments are at dawn.', 541, 0), (410620, 'All flesh shall perish together  and man shall turn again unto dust.', 5587, 0), (410621, 'Oh  why should the spirit of mortal be proud? Like a fast-flitting meteor  a fast-flying cloud  A flash of the lightning  a break of the wave  He passes from life to his rest in the grave.', 3060, 0), (410622, 'The mother of all living.', 5587, 0), (410623, 'She''s somebody''s mother  boys  you know  For all she''s aged and poor and slow.', 64774, 0), (410624, 'A mother is a mother still  The holiest thing alive.', 18724, 0), (410625, 'Men are what their mothers made them.', 760, 0), (410626, 'What is home without a mother?', 64440, 0), (410627, 'There is none  In all this cold and hollow world  no fount Of deep strong  deathless love  save that within A mother''s heart.', 62925, 0), (410628, 'If I were hanged on the highest hill  Mother o'' mine  O mother o'' mine! I know whose love would follow me still  Mother o'' mine  O mother o'' mine!', 843, 0), (410629, 'All that I am or hope to be  I owe to my angel mother.', 1012, 0), (410630, 'I arose a mother in Israel.', 5587, 0), (410631, 'The bravest battle that ever was fought  Shall I tell you where and when? On the maps of the world you will find it not  It was fought by the mothers of men.', 62874, 0), (410632, 'Who ran to help me when I fell  And would some pretty story tell  Or kiss the place to make it well? My Mother.', 64775, 0), (410633, 'For the hand that rocks the cradle Is the hand that rules the world.', 64776, 0),