y is a stage play with the parts written for instruments instead of for actors.', 10511, 0), (410919, 'An ear for music is very different from a taste for music. I have no ear whatever  I could not sing an air to save my life  but I have the intensest delight in music  and can detect good from bad.', 1910, 0), (410920, 'Classic music is th'' kind that we keep thinkin''ll turn into a tune.', 64804, 0), (410921, 'Discord occasions a momentary distress to the ear  which remains unsatisfied  and even uneasy  until it hears something better.', 64805, 0), (410922, 'Discord occasions a momentary distress to the ear  which remains unsatisfied  and even uneasy  until it hears something better. I am convinced...that provided the ear be at length made amends  there are few dissonances too strong for it. Disharmony  to paraphrase Bergson''s statement about disorder  is simply a harmony to which many are unaccustomed.', 1931, 0), (410923, 'Canned music is like audible wallpaper.', 48832, 0), (410924, 'Don''t play what''s there  play what''s not there.', 19793, 0), (410925, 'From Mozart I learnt to say important things in a conversational way.', 266, 0), (410926, 'Generally music feedeth that disposition of the spirits which it findeth.', 1035, 0), (410927, 'God tells me how he wants the music played - and you get in his way.', 64717, 0), (410928, 'Handel was a man of the world  but Bach was a world of a man.', 64806, 0), (410929, 'He was dying all his life.', 7846, 0), (410930, 'I am sure my music has a taste of codfish in it.', 63669, 0), (410931, 'I do not mind what language an opera is sung in so long as it is the language I don''t understand.', 64807, 0), (410932, 'In the Negro melodies of America I find all that is needed for a great and noble school of music.', 64808, 0), (410933, 'It is the best of all trades to make songs  and the second best to sing them.', 4439, 0), (410934, 'Jazz came to America 300 years ago in chains.', 64809, 0), (410935, 'Jazz is about the only fo